--- !u!114 &738002364
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_PrefabParentObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInternal: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 738002363}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 92471cc1733c49042be56cd39b4b6e5e, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  text: 'BipedIK is essentially just a pre-defined setup for a collection of IK solvers
    for biped characters. You could just as well have individual LimbIK/AimIK/LookAtIK
    components on the character, BipedIK just simplifies the setup process.


    Compared to FullBodyBipedIK (FBBIK) it is much faster to use BipedIK, but of course
    it does not have the full body effect. Since FinalIK 0.4 you are able to set FBBIK
    iteration count to 0, in which case the full body will not be calculated and it
    will behave similar to BipedIK with similar performance. It is ideal for optimizing
    IK for low priority characters.


    Right-click on any FinalIK component header and select "User Manual" or "Script
    Reference" for more info.'
